cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision, specifically on the problem of local feature detection. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel approach using machine learning techniques, specifically regression and deep neural networks, which suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the theoretical analysis of local features in terms of geometric transformations, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper's focus on learning and optimization could also place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
